usage.en: The recommended controlled vocabulary is the Collection visibility code list.
The recommended controlled vocabulary is the Estimation Procedure type code list.

description.en: The attribute or column in which a distribution is structured.
A classification of the attribute.

usage.en: The recommended controlled vocabulary is the Feature type code list.

description.en: The label of the attribute.
An explanation of the attribute.

usage.en: The recommended controlled vocabulary is the Flow status code list.
The recommended controlled vocabulary is the Flow Parameter type code list.

description.en: The degree or extent of something, as determined by measurement or calculation.

usage.en: The recommended controlled vocabulary is the Prediction Feature type code list.

description.en: A computed characteristic that describes a distribution.
A title of the quality.
A computed value of the quality.

usage.en: The recommended controlled vocabulary is the Task type code list.

description.en: A legal document giving official permission to do something with a resource.
A catalogue or repository that hosts the Datasets or Data Services being described.
This property refers to a site or end-point (Data Service) that is listed in the Catalogue.

usage.en: As empty Catalogues are usually indications of problems, this property should be combined with the previous property dataset to implement an empty Catalogue check.

description.en: This property refers to a Catalogue Record that is part of the Catalogue.

This property links the Catalogue with a Dataset that is part of the Catalogue. As empty Catalogues are usually indications of problems, this property should be combined with the next property service to implement an empty Catalogue check.
This property contains a name given to the Catalogue. This property can be repeated for parallel language versions of the name.
This property refers to an entity (organisation) responsible for making the Catalogue available.
This property contains a free-text account of the Catalogue. This property can be repeated for parallel language versions of the description.
A description of a Datasets entry in the Catalogue.
This property links the Catalogue Record to the Dataset, Data service or Catalog described in the record.
This property contains the most recent date on which the Catalogue entry was changed or modified.
This property contains a free-text account of the record. This property can be repeated for parallel language versions of the description.
It refers to the version of the description. '1' for original version.
A collection of operations that provides access to one or more datasets or data processing functions.
This property refers to a collection of data that this data service can distribute.
The root location or primary endpoint of the service (an IRI).
This property contains a name given to the Data Service. This property can be repeated for parallel language versions of the name.
A conceptual entity that represents the information published.
This property contains a version number or other version designation of the Dataset.

This property refers to a web page that provides access to the Dataset, its Distributions and/or additional information. It is intended to point to a landing page at the original data provider, not to a page on a site of a third party, such as an aggregator.
This property contains a keyword or tag describing the Dataset.
This property links the Dataset to an available Distribution.
The status of the dataset in the context of the publication process.

usage.en: The recommended controlled vocabulary is the Dataset status code list.

description.en: This property contains a name given to the Dataset. This property can be repeated for parallel language versions of the name.
This property refers to an entity (organisation) responsible for making the Dataset available.
This property contains the date of formal issuance (e.g., publication) of the Dataset.
This property refers to a related Dataset of which the described Dataset is a version, edition, or adaptation.
This property is about a related resource, such as a publication, that references, cites, or otherwise points to the dataset.
This property contains the main identifier for the Dataset, e.g. the URI or other unique identifier in the context of the Catalogue.
This property refers to a related Dataset that is a version, edition, or adaptation of the described Dataset.
This property contains a free-text account of the Dataset. This property can be repeated for parallel language versions of the description.
This property refers to the  entity responsible for producing the dataset.
People who contributed to the current version of the datadat (e.g. reformatting)
This property refers to information that indicates whether the Dataset is open data, has access restrictions or is not public.

usage.en: The recommended controlled vocabulary is the Access Rights Named Authority List.

description.en: Version label provided by user, something relevant to the user. Can also be a date, hash, or some other type of id.
Date of processing.
The date the data was originally collected, given by the uploader.
Who can see the dataset. Typical values: 'Everyone','All my friends','Only me'. Can also be any of the user's circles.

usage.en: The recommended controlled vocabulary is the Dataset visibility code list.

description.en: A physical embodiment of the Dataset in a particular format.
This property refers to the policy expressing the rights associated with the distribution if using the ODRL vocabulary.
This property contains a URL that is a direct link to a downloadable file in a given format.
This property contains the size of a Distribution in bytes.
This property contains a URL that gives access to a Distribution of the Dataset. The resource at the access URL may contain information about how to get the Dataset.
This property refers to a data service that gives access to the distribution of the dataset.
This property provides a mechanism that can be used to verify that the contents of a distribution have not changed. The checksum is related to the downloadURL.
This property contains a name given to the Distribution. This property can be repeated for parallel language versions of the description.
This property refers to the licence under which the Distribution is made available.
This property refers to a language used in the Distribution. This property can be repeated if the metadata is provided in multiple languages.

usage.en: The recommended controlled vocabulary is the EU Vocabularies Languages Named Authority List.

description.en: File identifier
This property refers to the file format of the Distribution.

usage.en: The recommended controlled vocabulary is the EU Vocabularies File Type Named Authority List.

description.en: The attribute that represents the row-id column, if present in the dataset.
Warnings while processing the dataset.
Errors discovered while processing the dataset.
Attributes that should be excluded in modelling, such as identifiers and indexes.
A computed characteristic that describes a distribution.
The attribute or column being part of a distribution.
The default target attribute, if it exists.

usage.en: Can also have multiple values (comma-separated). Of course, tasks can be defined that use another attribute as target.

description.en: Any entity carrying out actions with respect to the (Core) entities Catalogue, Datasets, Data Services and Distributions. If the Agent is an organisation, the use of the Organization Ontology is recommended.
This property contains a name of the agent. This property can be repeated for different versions of the name (e.g. the name in different languages)
